The basic hypothesis of this study is that anaerobic granular sludge and aerobic biofilms supported by a hybrid vertical anaerobic biofilm ( HyVAB® ) reactor design (
Figure 1
) are the most robust combined niches for microorganisms to treat inhibitory substances , since microbial aggregates protect the microorganisms against such substances as they are delivered slowly by diffusion from the liquid phase .
